; framemonitor.cfg — FrameMonitor launch configuration
;
; SETUP: copy this file to framemonitor.cfg in the project root (or next to
; the compiled executable) and uncomment exactly one active entry below.
;
; Lines beginning with ; or # are comments.
; The first uncommented 'video=' or 'camera=' entry wins.
;
; If this file is absent or contains no active entry, a file-open dialog
; will appear on startup so you can choose a video interactively.


; ── Video file mode ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
; Provide the full path to a video recording of the incubator.
; Any format OpenCV can open is accepted (.mts, .mp4, .avi, .mkv, .mov, …).
;
; video=C:\recordings\recording1.mts
; video=C:\recordings\recording2.mts


; ── Live camera mode ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
; Set the index of the capture device reported by your OS (0 = first camera).
; Run the DeviceEnumerator utility (see DeviceEnumerator.h) to list devices.
;
; camera=0


; ── Output directory ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
; Directory where all output files are written:
;   <videoname>.md        — detected breath positions
;   <videoname>.sig.md    — per-frame signal data
;   <videoname>.res.md    — computed breath rate results
;   op<videoname>.mp4     — annotated combined output video  (if bSaveVid)
;   sepop<videoname>.mp4  — annotated separate output video  (if bSaveVid)
;
; If absent, files are written relative to the current working directory,
; which is usually the project root when running from inside Visual Studio —
; uncomment and set this to a dedicated results folder to keep the repo clean.
;
; output_dir=C:\Users\YourName\Documents\FrameMonitor\results
